quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  18,60,"Remember when Moses said to his servant, \"I will not stop till I reach the confluence of the two seas, or for years will I journey on"
  18,61,"But when they reached their confluence, they forgot their fish, and it took its way in the sea at will"
  18,62,"And when they had passed on, said Moses to his servant, \"Bring us our morning meal; for now have we incurred weariness from this journey"
  18,63,"He said, \"What thinkest thou? When we repaired to the rock for rest I forgot the fish; and none but Satan made me forget it, so as not to mention it; and it hath taken its way in the sea in a wondrous sort"
  18,64,"He said, \"It is this we were in quest of.\" And they both went back retracing their footsteps"
  18,65,"Then found they one of our servants to whom we had vouchsafed our mercy, and whom we had instructed with our knowledge"
  18,66,"And Moses said to him, \"Shall I follow thee that thou teach me, for guidance, of that which thou too hast been taught"
  18,67,"He said, \"Verily, thou canst not have patience with me"
  18,68,How canst thou be patient in matters whose meaning thou comprehendest not
  18,69,"He said, \"Thou shalt find me patient if God please, nor will I disobey thy bidding"
  18,70,"He said, \"Then, if thou follow me, ask me not of aught until I have given thee an account thereof"